1
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:52,800
You always said your dad passed away.

2
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:55,520
I really wanted to ask

3
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:59,240
how he died.

4
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:01,800
He didn't die.

5
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:03,780
He ran away with his mistress.

6
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:07,060
My mom told my sister and me to pretend he's dead.

7
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:08,960
So I swore since I was a kid

8
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:10,660
that if I ever get married,

9
00:02:10,919 --> 00:02:13,250
I will never be as irresponsible as my dad.

10
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:15,080
I will treat them well for the rest of my life,

11
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:17,740
and pamper my wife and kids in the palm of my hand.

12
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:23,210
You're so young, why are you thinking about this?

13
00:02:23,880 --> 00:02:24,680
It's not far.

14
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:26,240
I've thought it through.

15
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:28,320
With my grades, I'll go to a junior college at best,

16
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:29,200
study for three years,

17
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:31,040
and get married right after graduation.

18
00:02:31,040 --> 00:02:33,400
As a man, settling down and starting a career,

19
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:34,530
I should definitely

20
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:36,200
settle down first.

21
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:38,960
My mom said after I finish my bachelor's degree,

22
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:40,079
she wants me to go to grad school.

23
00:02:40,079 --> 00:02:41,760
Otherwise, it'll be hard to find a job.

24
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:43,480
I guess if I get married,

25
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:46,060
it'll take another seven or eight years.

26
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:48,120
Eat your noodles.

27
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:49,450
They're getting soggy.

28
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:39,160
Grandma.

29
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:41,400
I'm sorry.

30
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:45,360
I couldn't come to see you one last time.

31
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,920
I went to a competition to win prize money.

32
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:52,160
I thought when I had the money,

33
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:55,440
I could pay for your surgery.

34
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:01,400
You go ahead.

35
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:04,370
I want to stay with Grandma for a while.

36
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:08,840
I'll wait for you outside.

37
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:09,720
No need.

38
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:11,780
You should go back.

39
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:15,320
Yuanbao.

40
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:17,320
Right now,

41
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:23,100
I don't really want to see you.

42
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:32,840
I understand.

43
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,280
I know.

44
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:40,960
Then stay safe,

45
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:42,960
and go home early.

46
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,480
I didn't dare to be too far from her,

47
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:37,320
yet I didn't dare to go up and greet her.

48
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:41,760
I was afraid seeing me would bring back sad memories.

49
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:44,050
And even more afraid

50
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:47,130
that she hated me from the bottom of her heart.

51
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:50,320
I knew he wasn't far away.

52
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:53,000
I didn't know how to face him now.

53
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,580
I was afraid I wouldn't control my emotions and would hurt him.

54
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,600
Although we were close,

55
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:01,200
it felt like there was

56
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:03,180
an uncrossable chasm between us.

57
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:05,600
Though invisible and intangible,

58
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:07,960
I knew the barrier was there.

59
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,080
Our friendship of over ten years

60
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:12,800
was now like a rainbow bubble in the sun.

61
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:15,360
Still beautiful,

62
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:18,840
but so fragile it could burst at any moment.

63
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:26,160
Champion. Champion. Champion.

64
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:27,600
The champion is back.

65
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:30,040
Welcome, champion. Welcome, champion.

66
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:31,440
Welcome, champion.

67
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,159
Welcome, champion.

68
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:36,400
Welcome, champion.

69
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:38,280
Welcome, champion.

70
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:55,850
Hello, Mr. Xu and Mr. Zhong.

71
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,130
Come, who wants this candy?

72
00:06:58,280 --> 00:06:59,800
I do, I do, I do.

73
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:04,680
Is Mr. Tian married with children?

74
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:06,620
Those are the orphans he adopted.

75
00:07:07,320 --> 00:07:09,250
Mr. Tian pays for their education.

76
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,800
Mr. Tian is such a role model.

77
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:14,160
Even though he's poor as a church mouse,

78
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,160
look at his shoes.

79
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:17,080
And he's an older bachelor.

80
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:18,680
But when it comes to charity,

81
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:20,440
he doesn't hold back at all.

82
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:22,960
How come I didn't hear about it before?

83
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:24,360
Mr. Tian is very low-key.

84
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,930
He didn't tell anyone else either.

85
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:30,960
His children only come back to visit him once a year.

86
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:38,840
Good, here's another reward for you.

87
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:40,170
Come on, it's your turn.

88
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:50,020
There is something

89
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,360
I haven't had the chance to thank you for.

90
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:53,080
What is it?

91
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:56,020
When my grandmother was in the hospital,

92
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:57,920
you helped me so much.

93
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:00,800
I really don't know how to thank you.

94
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,090
You're welcome.

95
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:04,480
Isn't this what I'm supposed to do?

96
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:08,840
Nothing in this world is a given.

97
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,200
I mean,

98
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,600
whatever someone does for another in this world

99
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,040
shouldn't be taken for granted.

100
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:19,080
I have taken your kindness to heart.

101
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:22,360
I will slowly pay you back in the future.

102
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,660
I didn't expect you to pay me back.

103
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:28,760
No, I don't want to owe anyone anything.

104
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:30,520
If you don't let me pay you back,

105
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:32,400
I'll feel really bad.

106
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,840
I really don't know what to do with you.

107
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,700
So how are you going to pay me back?

108
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:40,720
How about...

109
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:48,240
How about you buy me a cup of milk tea?

110
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:51,320
Just one cup of milk tea?

111
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:53,160
Two cups wouldn't be bad either.

112
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:54,460
Three cups.

113
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:55,520
It's a deal.

114
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,440
It's a deal.

115
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:00,720
Let's go.

116
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:30,930
Remember to eat breakfast.

117
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:20,400
Ms. Tian, what's wrong?

118
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:22,040
My bike chain fell off.

119
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:49,880
Mr. Xu, you're amazing.

120
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:51,200
How can I thank you?

121
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:53,560
No need to thank me.

122
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:55,570
You're pretty amazing too.

123
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:57,680
Thanks.

124
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:00,920
If your chain falls off again,

125
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:04,080
you'll have to date me.

126
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:04,840
Okay.

127
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:10,200
Date you?

128
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:11,640
M-Mr. Xu.

129
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:27,300
You're looking for me?

130
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:31,120
I noticed you haven't come over for dinner lately.

131
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,800
I'm quite worried about you.

132
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:34,640
Are you doing okay?

133
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:36,840
I'm fine.

134
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:39,520
Anything else?

135
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:42,520
Well...

136
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:46,200
I... I see you've been

137
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:49,320
getting close to Meng Jingu lately.

138
00:12:49,760 --> 00:12:50,600
Are you two...

139
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:52,720
We agreed

140
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:55,240
to apply for universities in Beijing together.

141
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:57,800
So he is continuing to tutor me.

142
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:00,120
No.

143
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:04,160
Didn't we agree to go to Beijing together?

144
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:08,720
Did we? Did I say that?

145
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:11,890
I probably don't remember.

146
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:14,680
I think it's better for you to go abroad.

147
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:16,000
I'm not going abroad.

148
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:18,250
I've discussed it with my parents.

149
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:19,560
I'm not leaving.

150
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:23,490
All these years,

151
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:26,570
I've always treated you as my own brother.

152
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:32,600
I did before, and I still do now.

153
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:38,520
I can't leave.

154
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:40,680
We are family.

155
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,600
We agreed to stick together.

156
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,400
I promised Grandma I'd take care of you for the rest of my life.

157
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:46,440
I can't leave.

158
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:50,580
What nonsense are you talking about?

159
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:54,720
Even biological brothers don't take care of each other for a whole lifetime.

160
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:55,560
Besides...

161
00:13:58,440 --> 00:14:01,040
Besides, we've never been family.

162
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:02,440
Yuanbao.

163
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:09,080
Yuanbao.

164
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:13,120
So you are here.

165
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:15,020
I've been looking for you.

166
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:16,640
Why are you here?

167
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,330
Didn't I tell you to wait in the classroom?

168
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:23,520
Qingyun, you're here too.

169
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:26,120
Well,

170
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:30,000
I have something to do, so I won't bother you.

171
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:31,920
I'll get going.

172
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,280
Qingyun.

173
00:14:56,320 --> 00:14:57,920
I don't know what to say.

174
00:14:58,720 --> 00:14:59,980
At first, I thought...

175
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:03,120
I thought you were going to take the college entrance examination with everyone.

176
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:04,000
I didn't expect

177
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:06,200
you'd leave so suddenly.

178
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:08,120
But going abroad is a good thing.

179
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:11,560
I wish you a bright future and academic success.

180
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:13,720
When you return to China,

181
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:15,340
come back and visit often.

182
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:16,880
Mr. Tian,

183
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:21,880
I've caused you a lot of trouble these past few years.

184
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:24,960
I'm sorry.

185
00:15:34,520 --> 00:15:35,780
I'm already used to it.

186
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:38,640
Isn't this a characteristic of your age group?

187
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:41,440
But

188
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:43,240
if you leave,

189
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,320
what will happen to Yuanbao?

190
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,640
I'm saying goodbye to everyone today.

191
00:16:02,640 --> 00:16:04,370
I'm really glad you could come.

192
00:16:05,360 --> 00:16:07,020
What are you looking at me for?

193
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:08,330
Drink up, everyone.

194
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:09,360
Drink up.

195
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:10,400
Brother, stop drinking.

196
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:11,320
You can't drink like this.

197
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:12,160
Drink less.

198
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:16,600
All right.

199
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:18,440
Even though we are eighteen,

200
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:20,530
we still have school tomorrow.

201
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:23,040
I forgot.

202
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:25,450
I dropped out of school.

203
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:27,520
You still have to go to school.

204
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:28,440
You don't need to drink.

205
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:29,640
Don't drink alcohol.

206
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:30,560
Here are some drinks.

207
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:31,960
Tea and cola.

208
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:33,760
Help yourselves.

209
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:40,880
I'm really glad you could come to see me off.

210
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:43,800
Zhang Dongbo, thank you.

211
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:46,120
Shang Ningyu, thank you.

212
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:49,400
Ruirui, thank you.

213
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:51,680
Qiao Yan, thank you.

214
00:16:52,280 --> 00:16:54,520
Class Monitor Xing Yaqi, thank you.

215
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:59,280
Wang Zhiyong, PE rep, thank you.

216
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:02,520
Gao Jingyi, thank you.

217
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:07,800
I envy you.

218
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:24,500
Why are you all looking like that?

219
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:26,160
I'm just going abroad.

220
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:28,440
It's not like I'm never coming back.

221
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:30,440
Don't look so sad, you hear me?

222
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:32,520
Let's be happy today.

223
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:34,970
So I can leave with peace of mind, okay?

224
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:37,240
Come, let's drink.

225
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:40,400
Why don't you sing a song? I'll pick one for you.

226
00:18:20,120 --> 00:18:21,480
Listen up.

227
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:23,360
After I leave,

228
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:26,440
take good care of Xiong Yuanbao for me.

229
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:29,720
If I find out anyone is bullying her,

230
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,060
I'll kill them when I get back.

231
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:08,250
What did you say?

232
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:11,480
Take good care of Yuanbao.

233
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:21,200
Qingyun.

234
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:22,520
Qingyun.

235
00:19:25,120 --> 00:19:26,880
Yuanbao, you're here.

236
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:36,640
He drank a lot.

237
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:39,600
He kept shouting your name,

238
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:41,480
so they called you.

239
00:19:43,280 --> 00:19:43,840
Mutou.

240
00:19:44,680 --> 00:19:45,200
Mutou.

241
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:47,480
He's already dead drunk.

242
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:50,200
Let's take him home.

243
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:17,480
Yuan...

244
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:19,560
Yuanbao,

245
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:22,160
is that you?

246
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:30,600
Yuanbao.

247
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:33,680
Yuanbao, I'm sorry.

248
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:36,720
It's all my fault.

249
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:39,920
It's all my fault.

250
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:43,360
Don't blame me.

251
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:46,320
I don't want to leave.

252
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:49,360
I'm sorry.

253
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:54,440
We'll be home in a while.

254
00:20:56,120 --> 00:20:57,380
Sleep a little longer.

255
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:01,600
No.

256
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:06,880
I'm afraid you won't be here when I wake up.

257
00:21:08,760 --> 00:21:11,840
Yuanbao, I regret it.

258
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:14,200
I'm not leaving.

259
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:17,500
I'm going to stay and take care of you.

260
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:23,200
I will spend the rest of my life making it up to you.

261
00:21:24,360 --> 00:21:25,400
What I owe you,

262
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:27,120
what I owe Grandma,

263
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:29,360
what I owe your parents,

264
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,400
I will make it up to you all.

265
00:21:33,160 --> 00:21:35,880
I beg you, don't let me go.

266
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,600
Please.

267
00:21:45,080 --> 00:21:45,960
Don't cry.

268
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:49,560
Your head will hurt if you keep crying.

269
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:54,170
Come on, get some sleep.

270
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:31,760
All right.

271
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:50,640
Yuanbao!

272
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:52,960
Yuanbao!

273
00:22:57,320 --> 00:22:58,920
She probably went to school.

274
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:05,520
Let's go.

275
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:07,780
Don't miss the flight.

276
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:53,640
Driver, stop the car.

277
00:23:59,640 --> 00:24:02,200
Mom, Dad.

278
00:24:02,680 --> 00:24:03,800
Give me some time.

279
00:24:35,560 --> 00:24:36,200
Yuanbao!

280
00:24:36,320 --> 00:24:37,180
Xiong Yuanbao!

281
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:38,240
Open the door!

282
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:39,840
Open the door!

283
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:41,100
I know you're home!

284
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:42,680
You... Open the door!

285
00:24:43,160 --> 00:24:44,320
Open the door!

286
00:24:45,560 --> 00:24:46,840
Open the door!

287
00:24:48,560 --> 00:24:49,360
I can't...

288
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:50,720
I can't leave.

289
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:53,400
I can't leave you at home alone.

290
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:54,640
Yuanbao!

291
00:24:54,760 --> 00:24:56,560
What will you do alone, Yuanbao?

292
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:58,240
Yuanbao!

293
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:02,280
I promised Grandma.

294
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:07,100
I promised Grandma I'd take good care of you.

295
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:09,600
Open the door!

296
00:25:11,480 --> 00:25:12,720
Xiong Yuanbao!

297
00:25:13,760 --> 00:25:17,280
I beg you. Open the door!

298
00:25:36,840 --> 00:25:38,760
Open the door!

299
00:25:57,080 --> 00:25:58,040
I get it.

300
00:26:00,320 --> 00:26:01,720
Only if we leave

301
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:05,720
can you forget

302
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:08,240
those painful memories.

303
00:26:09,320 --> 00:26:10,000
Okay.

304
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:11,480
I'll leave.

305
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:14,330
Are you going or not?

306
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:16,000
Wait a moment, sir.

307
00:27:06,360 --> 00:27:08,090
How do you solve this question?

308
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:34,080
You two were so close back then.

309
00:27:34,240 --> 00:27:36,770
I thought something was going on between you.

310
00:27:37,040 --> 00:27:38,240
Besides, the rumors outside

311
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:39,500
are spreading wildly.

312
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:44,050
That's exactly what a rumor is.

313
00:27:45,160 --> 00:27:46,320
Rumors are all fake.

314
00:27:46,560 --> 00:27:47,680
What do you mean?

315
00:27:51,960 --> 00:27:53,690
Are you really going to do that?

316
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:00,440
I don't want to hold him back.

317
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:03,860
I want him to let go of everything here

318
00:28:04,600 --> 00:28:07,560
and pursue the better life that should belong to him.

319
00:28:08,240 --> 00:28:10,880
Even brothers don't take care of each other for a lifetime.

320
00:28:10,880 --> 00:28:11,600
Besides.

321
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:17,280
Besides, we were never a family.

322
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:26,400
Yuanbao.

323
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:33,920
Actually, I've always liked you.

324
00:28:48,520 --> 00:28:49,160
Yuanbao.

325
00:28:49,280 --> 00:28:50,140
Xiong Yuanbao.

326
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:51,200
Open the door.

327
00:28:51,720 --> 00:28:52,800
Open the door.

328
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:54,160
I know you're at home.

329
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,640
Open the door.

330
00:28:56,120 --> 00:28:57,280
Open the door.

331
00:28:58,520 --> 00:28:59,600
Open the door.

332
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:02,320
I can't

333
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:03,680
leave.

334
00:29:04,120 --> 00:29:06,360
I can't leave you alone at home.

335
00:29:06,680 --> 00:29:07,440
Yuanbao.

336
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:46,120
Today I heard a very unfamiliar word,

337
00:29:46,280 --> 00:29:47,440
autism.

338
00:29:47,560 --> 00:29:48,840
I don't know why.

339
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:50,880
Ever since Uncle and Aunt passed away,

340
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:53,400
Yuanbao refuses to speak to anyone anymore.

341
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:54,640
These days,

342
00:29:54,680 --> 00:29:57,760
I tried many ways to coax Yuanbao into speaking,

343
00:29:58,200 --> 00:30:00,000
but she just won't open her mouth.

344
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,120
What should I do?

345
00:30:01,280 --> 00:30:03,600
I need to find a way to coax her.

346
00:30:03,640 --> 00:30:05,400
Yuanbao, I don't know how.

347
00:30:05,440 --> 00:30:07,160
Can you teach me?

348
00:30:07,400 --> 00:30:09,120
Yuanbao, I really don't know how to do this.

349
00:30:09,120 --> 00:30:10,600
Please teach me.

350
00:30:11,640 --> 00:30:13,480
I finally succeeded.

351
00:30:13,560 --> 00:30:15,520
As long as I ask her to explain problems to me,

352
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:16,960
she's willing to talk.

353
00:31:59,560 --> 00:32:00,160
Boss.

354
00:32:02,680 --> 00:32:03,520
Wait a moment.

355
00:32:10,960 --> 00:32:11,400
Here.

356
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:12,120
Thank you.

357
00:32:49,120 --> 00:32:51,560
If you're not in the group photo,

358
00:32:51,880 --> 00:32:53,400
what's the point?
